author: The Virginian-Pilot
title: Wednesday's roundup | Barackman leads Kellam to golf title
text:
6A South tournament Kellam finished with a team score of 322 to win the region tournament at Magnolia Green near Midlothian.
The Knights were led by Cam Barackman, who shot 76, along with Leonard Park (78), Dylan Martin (80) and Matt Wawner (88). Kellam advanced to the state tournament with Riverbend (324) which outlasted First Colonial and Franklin County in a playoff after the three teams tied for second.
Cosby's Rob Witherspoon shot a 71 to claim the individual championship, two strokes ahead of Landstown's Brandon Kelly.
Other locals to qualify for the state tournament were First Colonial's Teddy Hoffman (74) and Landstown's Raphael Olfato (77). Olfato defeated Western Branch's Jordan Hill in a playoff after they finished tied for eighth.
First Colonial's Carley Rudolf finished in a three-way tie for sixth with a 76 and will compete in the 6A state girls' tournament.
Grassfield (331) finished sixth while Western Branch (345) finished eighth.
5A South tournament
Hickory's Patrick Gareiss (154) shot a final-round 76 to finish in a four-way tie for fourth in the two-round tournament at the Hamptons Golf Course to qualify for the state tournament.
Also qualifying was Kempsville's Ryan Oden (155), who finished in eighth. Deep Run's Adam Hade (146) took medalist honors, winning by six strokes.
In team competition, Deep Run (630) finished two strokes ahead of Mills Godwin to win the tournament. Hickory (696) finished in fifth and Maury (724) finished in seventh.
